reviewText: who doesn't like wonder woman?? the first season is great, set during WW2.. yes it's made in the 70's so the effects of course aren't the best but that doesn't change how cool the series is.. my daughter has watched the series at least 3 times and she loves it every time..

I watched this series when I was younger and thought my 4 yr old granddaughter might enjoy it as she was becoming interested in super heroes and especially Wonder Woman. Not only did she enjoy it, but the whole family enjoyed watching it as well.

Do not purchase these unless you want to buy glasses afterward.  This edition is a horrible transfer.  Go with the previous releases, not this one with SKU 883929586943.  This watered down crap should never have been released.  You definitely get what you pay for.  Again, THIS VERSION IS HORRIBLE.

*This review is solely for the disc quality, not the show.  Five stars for the show.
DVD is very good . fun for those  who are nostalgic for the 70's and Wonder Woman fans

I bought these DVDs on Ebay and the picture quality of the DVDs is awful. The first four episodes from the first season are included in one DVD including additional features. I don't recommend these DVDs if you're looking for picture quality.
